ECO563 | Economic Development II | http://www.econ.princeton.edu/ | instructors:Anne C. Case Angus S. Deaton description:Selected topics in the economic analysis of development beyond those covered in 562.  Topics are selected from the theory and measurement of poverty and inequality; the relationship between growth and poverty; health and education in economic development; saving, growth, population, and development; commodity prices in economic development.
